<h2>More Information About the Honey Bee (but not its knees)</h2>

<p>Apis cerana indica, the Indian honey bee, is a subspecies of Asiatic honey bee. It is one of the predominant bees found and domesticated in India, Pakistan, Nepal, Myanmar, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Thailand and mainland Asia. Relatively non-aggressive and rarely exhibiting swarming behavior, it is ideal for beekeeping.</p>

<p>It is similar to the European honey bee (Apis mellifera), which tends to be slightly larger and can be readily distinguished.</p>

